.TH "TEMPORAL.ZONEDDATETIME.DAYOFYEAR" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.ZonedDateTime.dayOfYear \-
Temporal.ZonedDateTime.prototype.dayOfYear
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]dayOfYear\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] instances returns a positive integer
representing the 1\-based day index in the year of this date.
The first day of this year is \f[CR]1\f[R], and the last day is the
\f[CR]daysInYear\f[R].
It is calendar\-dependent.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]dayOfYear\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
To create a new \f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] object with the
desired new \f[CR]dayOfYear\f[R] value, use the \f[CR]add()\f[R] or
\f[CR]subtract()\f[R] method with the appropriate number of
\f[CR]days\f[R].
.PP
For general information and more examples, see
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.dayOfYear\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using dayOfYear
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dt = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01[America/New_York]\(dq);
console.log(dt.dayOfYear); \f[I]// 182\f[R]
.EE
